From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2025 10:38:32 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 05/10] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:hostapd: Support for SP and
 Puncturing in EIRP API

The existing API 'hostapd_get_eirp_pwr' gives the regulatory power
for channels for a given 6 GHz power mode.
This API does not use AFC payload for calculating the EIRP power
for standard power (SP) mode. This API also does not have support
to calculate the EIRP power for Punctured channels.

To fix this, add support to this API to use AFC payload for
calculating the EIRP power for standard power (SP) mode.
For LPI and VLP power modes, continue to us the EIRP value from the
regulatory channel lists for the corresponding power mode.

For punctured channels, use effective bandwidth for calculation
of EIRP power.

Ensure that the EIRP power from the AFC payload is limited by the
regulatory power for the corresponding channel and power mode.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
